Handling the path for a file or directoty

relative path	starts from the CURRENT DIRECTORY
absolute path	starts from the topmost directory in the file system


os module (os stands for operating system)
	it provides functions for working with files and directories

os.getcwd()		returns the name of the current directory
			cwd stands for "current working directory" (like bash)

###os.path module
		https://docs.python.org/2/library/os.path.html#module-os.path


os.path.abspath()	finds the absolute path to a file
os.path.exists()	checks if a file or a directory exists.
			it is a logical function
os.path.isdir()		checks whether it's a directory
			it is a logical funtion
os.path.isfile()	checks whether it's a file
			it is a logical function
os.listdir()		returns a list of the files (and other directories) in the given directory



